<h1 class="title">Free-Will-Lens-As-Mental-Model</h1>
<p>
Things should make sense both in a world with and without free will. Look at things through the lens of people having and then of people NOT having free will.  Any worldview or ethical/political system should be be robust to the presence/absence of free will, given that we dont know for sure if we have it (although we probably dont)
</p>


<div id="outline-container-org2d8dad0" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org2d8dad0">Follow-ups</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2d8dad0">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Examples of where this is useful: for prison reform / your attitudes toward others.</li>
<li>Does a habit/practice make sense in both a world with and without free will.</li>
<li>We don't know if we really have free will. (although I would guess we probably don't).</li>
</ul>
